[
  {
    "id": "001",
    "name": "Vietnam",
    "img": "https://assets.appsmith.com/widgets/default.png",
    "description": "There are many wonderful places in Southeast Asia, but Vietnam may just be the most fascinating and diversified of them all. From its stunning natural landscapes and deep and occasionally tragic past to its cuisine which has earned itself a name twice the world over, Vietnam is both exotic and captivating. It is a nation of breathtaking natural beauty and cultural intricacies, of bustling megacities and hill-tribe settlements. During your Vietnam tour, the surreal landscape of limestone rocks from the deck of a wooden ship in Halong Bay, the world's most stunning cave systems in Phong Nha-Ke Bang National Park and the beautiful yellow town of Hoi An touches on the places that will steal your heart."
  },
  {
    "id": "002",
    "name": "Italy",
    "img": "https://assets.appsmith.com/widgets/default.png",
    "description": "From the Venetian canals, the cobbled alleys of Rome and Arno river that flows through Florence to the Tuscan vineyards connected by winding roads flanked by stunning stone-built towns, there isn't much that Italy doesn't do well. The north boasts breathtaking lakes, beautiful mountains and adventurous hiking and cycling trails. Venturing south through the iconic metropolises where fashion, art and Renaissance were born, you'll be introduced to the stunning villages of the Cinque Terre and Amalfi Coast, as well as the zestful island of Sicily. In the heel of the boot, you'll meet the cultural traditions that have stood unwavering for centuries. All this is before we've even touched on the endless feasts that await you. Expect your culinary soul to be ignited with each new destination on your Italy tour!"
  },
  {
    "id": "003",
    "name": "Fiji",
    "img": "https://assets.appsmith.com/widgets/default.png",
    "description": "Fiji is a 300-island paradise occupying a spot in the Pacific Ocean rich in intriguing cultures and ancient customs. The mere mention of Fiji often conjures images of exquisite beaches, tropical jungle, undersea marvels and fascinating cultures, and that's exactly what you'll find here. Only half of the 300-odd islands are inhabited, which means securing your very own private island escape guarantees intimate seclusion that you'd be hard pushed to find elsewhere. The heavenly glow of the Mamanucas and Yasawa Islands, Fiji's two most popular archipelagos, is best explored by island-hopping, snorkelling, stand-up paddleboarding, and cruising to remote atolls. However you decide to spend your Fiji tour, a hammock, a coconut and a very warm Fijian welcome are never far away."
  }
]

